  "texts": [
    "These could relate to allowing AI-enabled advice to have a lower position in a carefully designed clinical referral cascade, which ensures decisions in scenarios of risk are referred to highly experienced oncologists 113.",
    "Approaches could also include allowing AI-enabled insights to be provided to tumour boards, or even allowing AIenabled advice to have a seat on a tumour board does not surrender human thinking and final decision making 100, 125.",
    "Breakthrough, fast track programmes and 'airlock classifications'",
    "Limitations of the regulatory status quo: Technologically novel approaches can face particular regulatory burden associated with their novelty.",
    "Novel products can, by definition, have regulatory routes based on predicate devices closed off to them 126, may require special regulatory processes based on novelty alone 55, 126 and are likely to face bottlenecks in access to small number of regulatory approval bodies 39."
